  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This is a tracking issue to look into how far we can tweak our `SecondsPerSlot` parameter and still have a stable runtime. We can use this issue to track bottlenecks or critical failures as we reduce the slot duration and figure out what our current max-min scenario of `NumValidators` to `SecondsPerSlot` realistically is.\r\n\r\n- [x] Mock BLS verification and signature creation with a feature flag to eliminate the BLS outlier in performance analysis\r\n- [x] Optimize db.BlockRoots to return the keys in the db lookup instead of unmarshaling blocks and then computing their signing roots\r\n- [x] Change the call to db.Blocks to a db.View transaction instead of an unnecessary Batch call\r\n- [x] Batch save validator latest votes instead of a sequential save which is slow and does not leverage concurrency\r\n- [x] Batch save operations for blocks, head block root, and attestations in general",
